1
00:00:08,320 --> 00:00:14,389
Let me ask you: do you feel overwhelmed by
the constant stress and pressure of trading?

2
00:00:14,389 --> 00:00:15,839
You're not alone.

3
00:00:15,839 --> 00:00:21,610
Today we'll take a deep dive into the mental
health issues faced by traders and we'll explore

4
00:00:21,610 --> 00:00:26,850
the importance of prioritizing mental health
in the fast-paced world of trading.

5
00:00:26,850 --> 00:00:33,740
So, like, subscribe and stick around for the
full video.

6
00:00:33,740 --> 00:00:39,210
The prevalence of mental health issues among
traders

7
00:00:39,210 --> 00:00:42,680
Mental health issues, including stress, anxiety,
and even depression, are very common among

8
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:44,040
traders.

9
00:00:44,040 --> 00:00:49,181
The high-pressure nature of trading can take
a toll on your mental health, and you may

10
00:00:49,181 --> 00:00:54,609
face significant financial and professional
risks on a daily basis.

11
00:00:54,609 --> 00:01:00,769
This can lead to a range of mental health
problems, such as difficulty sleeping, anger,

12
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:02,860
and difficulty concentrating.

13
00:01:02,860 --> 00:01:08,790
In severe cases, you may also suffer from
burnout, a physical and emotional exhaustion

14
00:01:08,790 --> 00:01:10,570
and a lack of accomplishment.

15
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:16,900
If left unchecked, these mental health issues
can seriously impact your ability to trade

16
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:22,750
effectively and may even lead to more serious
problems.

17
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:30,040
The impact of cognitive bias in trading
A cognitive bias is a fancy word.

18
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:35,420
Think at it as a mental shortcut that your
brain takes in order to simplify processing

19
00:01:35,420 --> 00:01:36,420
information.

20
00:01:36,420 --> 00:01:42,950
These biases can lead to irrational decision-making,
and they can be problematic in the context

21
00:01:42,950 --> 00:01:47,570
of trading, where the ability to make sound
decisions is critical.

22
00:01:47,570 --> 00:01:53,240
There are many different types of cognitive
biases that can affect you, you face them

23
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:54,869
every day.

24
00:01:54,869 --> 00:01:56,780
Confirmation bias is one of them.

25
00:01:56,780 --> 00:02:03,250
That’s the tendency to seek out information
that confirms your preexisting beliefs.

26
00:02:03,250 --> 00:02:08,890
You want to short a market, and you look for
signs that agree with our existing beliefs

27
00:02:08,890 --> 00:02:12,450
and you’ll ignore information that contradicts
it.

28
00:02:12,450 --> 00:02:17,640
You see this breakout, and you ignore the
other signs indicating that this might not

29
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:21,110
be the best trade.

30
00:02:21,110 --> 00:02:23,680
Loss aversion bias is another one.

31
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:30,050
It refers to the tendency to prioritize avoiding
losses over maximizing gains.

32
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:34,400
It’s when you decide whether to close a
buy position you opened.

33
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:39,260
The price has been performing poorly, and
you are concerned that you could lose more

34
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:41,310
money if you leave it open.

35
00:02:41,310 --> 00:02:45,930
However, you are also aware that there is
a chance that the price could bounce back

36
00:02:45,930 --> 00:02:49,920
and that you could close it for a higher price
in the future.

37
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:55,319
Because of your loss aversion bias, you may
be more likely to close the trade right away

38
00:02:55,319 --> 00:03:01,460
in order to avoid the possibility of further
losses, even if this means giving up the chance

39
00:03:01,460 --> 00:03:04,989
to potentially make more money in the future.

40
00:03:04,989 --> 00:03:06,930
I still suffer from this.

41
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:10,180
It’s one of my biggest struggles in trading.

42
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:16,430
To avoid loss aversion bias, take a long-term
perspective: rather than focusing on the potential

43
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:22,599
for short-term losses, try to consider the
potential rewards over the long term.

44
00:03:22,599 --> 00:03:25,670
Also, use risk management strategies.

45
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:31,080
Implementing different strategies, with different
stop-loss orders can help to mitigate the

46
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:35,599
potential for losses and can make it easier
to manage risk.

47
00:03:35,599 --> 00:03:41,709
The importance of setting boundaries and taking
breaks in trading

48
00:03:41,709 --> 00:03:47,330
As a trader, it is important for you to set
boundaries and take breaks from trading in

49
00:03:47,330 --> 00:03:50,290
order to maintain your mental health.

50
00:03:50,290 --> 00:03:55,790
Trading is a demanding and stressful activity,
and it's easy to get caught up in the grind

51
00:03:55,790 --> 00:03:57,959
without taking breaks.

52
00:03:57,959 --> 00:04:04,110
However, this can lead to burnout and will
negatively impact your performance.

53
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:09,230
When I first started, I was trading 10-12
hours per day.

54
00:04:09,230 --> 00:04:13,640
Even when I was watching a movie, I’d still
thinking about it.

55
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:16,299
Setting boundaries in trading is very important.

56
00:04:16,299 --> 00:04:22,560
This involve setting limits on the amount
of time you spend trading and analyzing a

57
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:28,850
chart, as well as establishing clear lines
between this and your personal life.

58
00:04:28,850 --> 00:04:35,910
This involves setting specific times for trading,
and, mandatory, staying aside certain hours

59
00:04:35,910 --> 00:04:41,539
or days that are designated as "off limits"
for trading.

60
00:04:41,539 --> 00:04:47,190
Taking breaks is also essential for maintaining
a healthy work-life balance.

61
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:52,250
By making time for yourself and your personal
life, you’ll be able to maintain a fresh

62
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:56,600
perspective to your trading and stay focused
and motivated.

63
00:04:56,600 --> 00:05:03,220
Strategies for building resilience and coping
with setbacks in trading

64
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:09,320
As a trader, it is important to build resilience
and develop strategies for coping with setbacks

65
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:11,229
and losses.

66
00:05:11,229 --> 00:05:17,330
Here are a few things that I try to do to
stay resilient and bounce back from losses:

67
00:05:17,330 --> 00:05:19,080
First is to maintain perspective.

68
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:21,919
So you lost a trade on EUR/YEN.

69
00:05:21,919 --> 00:05:27,150
It can be very easy to get caught up in the
moment and lose sight of the bigger picture

70
00:05:27,150 --> 00:05:28,720
when you lose a trade.

71
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:34,919
I try to remind myself that losses are a natural
part of the trading process and that every

72
00:05:34,919 --> 00:05:38,319
trade is just one small piece of the puzzle.

73
00:05:38,319 --> 00:05:44,199
It's important to remember that trading is
just one part of your life and you shouldn’t

74
00:05:44,199 --> 00:05:45,569
let it consume you.

75
00:05:45,569 --> 00:05:51,229
It’s imperative to make time for other interests
and activities outside of the screen.

76
00:05:51,229 --> 00:05:54,250
I also try to stay positive.

77
00:05:54,250 --> 00:06:00,009
It's easy to get down on yourself after you
made a mistake and took a bad trade, but I

78
00:06:00,009 --> 00:06:05,770
try to stay positive and focus on the things
that I did well in the process.

79
00:06:05,770 --> 00:06:08,170
Seeking support is another step.

80
00:06:08,170 --> 00:06:14,220
If you’re struggling to cope with a setback
in trading, maybe try to reach out to friends,

81
00:06:14,220 --> 00:06:16,760
family, or other traders for support.

82
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:23,050
It can be helpful to talk with someone who
can offer a fresh perspective.

83
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:28,110
Of course, learning from your mistakes is
another step, I’ve talked about it many

84
00:06:28,110 --> 00:06:29,590
times.

85
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:34,860
After a setback, try to take a step back and
analyze what went wrong.

86
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:41,860
The link between mental health and risk-taking
in trading

87
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:46,430
From my trading journey, I’ve learned that
there is a strong link between my mental health

88
00:06:46,430 --> 00:06:49,479
and my risk-taking behavior.

89
00:06:49,479 --> 00:06:55,759
When I am feeling anxious or stressed, I tend
to be more risk-averse and taking on too much

90
00:06:55,759 --> 00:06:56,759
risk.

91
00:06:56,759 --> 00:07:03,910
I might use bigger stop losses, I might double
my exposure, trying to recover some losses.

92
00:07:03,910 --> 00:07:10,770
On the other hand, when I am feeling confident
and in control, I know how to manage my risk.

93
00:07:10,770 --> 00:07:17,289
I have also learned that my mental state can
affect my ability to make good decisions.

94
00:07:17,289 --> 00:07:23,220
When I am feeling overwhelmed or emotional,
it is harder for me to think clearly and analyze

95
00:07:23,220 --> 00:07:25,599
data objectively.

96
00:07:25,599 --> 00:07:31,430
This can lead to poor decisions that will
expose you to unnecessary risk.

97
00:07:31,430 --> 00:07:37,009
Revenge trading is the immediate result, when
you try to "get back" at the market and try

98
00:07:37,009 --> 00:07:40,770
to recover a trade that didn't go your way.

99
00:07:40,770 --> 00:07:46,849
So to manage the link between mental health
and risk-taking in your trading, try to pay

100
00:07:46,849 --> 00:07:49,870
attention to your emotional state.

101
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:56,289
This might involve setting time to relax and
de-stress, or avoiding making important decisions

102
00:07:56,289 --> 00:07:58,099
when you’re feeling emotional.

103
00:07:58,099 --> 00:08:04,180
The impact of technology and screen time on
mental health

104
00:08:04,180 --> 00:08:10,569
As a trader, you spend a lot of time in front
of screens, whether you’re analyzing data,

105
00:08:10,569 --> 00:08:14,009
executing trades, or tracking the markets.

106
00:08:14,009 --> 00:08:18,449
This can and will have a negative impact on
your mental health.

107
00:08:18,449 --> 00:08:23,180
As I said before, prolonged screen time was
my number one problem.

108
00:08:23,180 --> 00:08:26,240
I used to stay in front of the screen for
hours.

109
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:31,740
The constant flow of information and the pressure
to make quick decisions was overwhelming,

110
00:08:31,740 --> 00:08:38,200
and it was hard to disconnect from trading
when I was always connected.

111
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:43,979
To mitigate the negative effects of screen
time on your mental health, again, take breaks

112
00:08:43,979 --> 00:08:46,900
from trading whenever possible.

113
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:52,070
Making a conscious effort to look away from
the screen and focus on something else you

114
00:08:52,070 --> 00:08:53,390
enjoy.

115
00:08:53,390 --> 00:08:57,950
Try to make time for activities that don't
involve screens.

116
00:08:57,950 --> 00:09:03,709
My solution was to move to swing trading,
and spend less time day trading.

117
00:09:03,709 --> 00:09:10,990
Nowadays, I spend 2, maximum 3 hours per day
to trade, sometimes even less.

118
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:19,160
The impact of impulsive or reckless behavior
Impulsive or reckless behavior in trading

119
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:23,089
is another cause which will affect your mental
health.

120
00:09:23,089 --> 00:09:29,760
This refers to making trades without a careful
consideration of the potential risks and rewards,

121
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:33,860
or disregarding risk management strategies.

122
00:09:33,860 --> 00:09:39,660
This type of behavior will lead to significant
losses and is mainly caused by your desire

123
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:44,680
for quick profits, or a lack of understanding
of the markets.

124
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:51,470
One way to avoid impulsive or reckless behavior
in trading is to develop a trading plan and

125
00:09:51,470 --> 00:09:53,120
stick to it.

126
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:59,640
This plan should include a clear set of rules
for entering and exiting trades, as well as

127
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:04,769
risk management strategies such as always
using stop-loss orders.

128
00:10:04,769 --> 00:10:11,650
It is also important to maintain a long-term
perspective and resist the temptation to chase

129
00:10:11,650 --> 00:10:13,060
after quick profits.

130
00:10:13,060 --> 00:10:17,050
So what you lost 2 trades today.

131
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:23,589
Markets will open tomorrow, and the next day,
and there are plenty of other opportunities.

132
00:10:23,589 --> 00:10:30,600
Be aware of your own emotional state and recognize
when it might be affecting your decision-making.

133
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:37,840
And it is also important to continuously educate
yourself about the markets and to stay up

134
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:42,839
to date on latest events that can impact the
markets.

135
00:10:42,839 --> 00:10:48,620
This will help to ensure that trading decisions
are based on a sound understanding of the

136
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:52,120
markets rather than on impulsive or reckless
behavior.

137
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:58,329
Dealing with the ups and downs of trading
and maintaining a positive attitude

138
00:10:58,329 --> 00:11:04,900
It is natural to feel upset or discouraged
after a trading loss, and it’s challenging

139
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:09,639
to maintain a positive attitude in the face
of such setbacks.

140
00:11:09,639 --> 00:11:15,029
I know it’s hard to be happy when you just
lost $1000 on a single trade.

141
00:11:15,029 --> 00:11:20,350
But if you want to remain in the game for
the long term, it is important to try to maintain

142
00:11:20,350 --> 00:11:24,769
a positive attitude and to keep things in
perspective.

143
00:11:24,769 --> 00:11:30,519
Reflect on each losing trade and rather than
dwelling on the negative, try to objectively

144
00:11:30,519 --> 00:11:35,170
evaluate what happened and what could have
been done differently.

145
00:11:35,170 --> 00:11:42,070
Also, set small, achievable goals: Rather
than trying to double your account in one

146
00:11:42,070 --> 00:11:46,730
month, try setting small, achievable goals
for yourself.

147
00:11:46,730 --> 00:11:50,769
Go for a 5-10% increase.

148
00:11:50,769 --> 00:11:55,950
This can help to give you a sense of control
and can increase confidence in your trading

149
00:11:55,950 --> 00:11:56,950
abilities.

150
00:11:56,950 --> 00:12:03,270
The impact of social isolation on mental health
in trading

151
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:09,290
Trading can be a solitary task and this can
lead to social isolation and a lack of social

152
00:12:09,290 --> 00:12:13,380
support, which can have negative consequences
for our mental health.

153
00:12:13,380 --> 00:12:18,630
I’m an introvert, and I don’t mind this
time alone with myself.

154
00:12:18,630 --> 00:12:24,670
But prolonged trading hours can lead to feelings
of loneliness and isolation, which can lead

155
00:12:24,670 --> 00:12:30,959
to other dangerous mental health problems
such as anxiety and even depression.

156
00:12:30,959 --> 00:12:36,160
To mitigate the negative impact of social
isolation on mental health when trading, it

157
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:43,320
is important to make an effort to stay connected
with other traders and seek out social support.

158
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:49,649
This might involve joining a trading community
or networking group, spending time with friends

159
00:12:49,649 --> 00:12:53,801
and family, or participating in activities
outside of trading.

160
00:12:53,801 --> 00:13:03,580
The fine line between trading and gambling
There’s a fine line between trading and

161
00:13:03,580 --> 00:13:04,580
gambling.

162
00:13:04,580 --> 00:13:10,459
Both involve taking a financial risk in the
hopes of achieving a profit, but there are

163
00:13:10,459 --> 00:13:13,589
some key differences between the two.

164
00:13:13,589 --> 00:13:19,959
When you trade, you’re making informed decisions
based on market analysis, risk management,

165
00:13:19,959 --> 00:13:21,470
and a clear strategy.

166
00:13:21,470 --> 00:13:27,110
It is a form of investment that requires discipline,
skill, and knowledge.

167
00:13:27,110 --> 00:13:33,010
Gambling, on the other hand, is mostly based
on chance and is not backed by any form of

168
00:13:33,010 --> 00:13:35,040
analysis or strategy.

169
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:38,399
And it can be highly addictive.

170
00:13:38,399 --> 00:13:43,370
When these 2 concepts are not clear, your
mental health will suffer.

171
00:13:43,370 --> 00:13:48,850
You must know the difference between trading
and gambling, and it is important to be aware

172
00:13:48,850 --> 00:13:52,079
of your own motivations and goals.

173
00:13:52,079 --> 00:13:58,029
If you’re making informed and rational decisions
based on a clear strategy, then you’re engaging

174
00:13:58,029 --> 00:13:59,029
in trading.

175
00:13:59,029 --> 00:14:06,550
However, if you’re trading based on emotions
or a desire for quick profits without a clear

176
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:10,290
plan, then you crossed the line into gambling.

177
00:14:10,290 --> 00:14:16,690
The danger of trading addiction

178
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:21,660
Trading addiction refers to a compulsive need
to trade, even when it is not in your best

179
00:14:21,660 --> 00:14:22,949
interest.

180
00:14:22,949 --> 00:14:28,320
This can be fueled by a variety of factors,
including the belief that you can get rich

181
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:34,589
quickly through trading, the thrill of the
markets, or maybe a desire to escape from

182
00:14:34,589 --> 00:14:35,920
other problems.

183
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:42,240
If you’re feeling an urge to trade constantly,
if you’re neglecting other responsibilities

184
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:47,940
in order to trade, if you’re continuing
to trade even when it is causing financial

185
00:14:47,940 --> 00:14:54,540
or personal problems, if you’re feeling
anxious or stressed when unable to trade,

186
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:57,759
then you may have problems with trading addiction.

187
00:14:57,759 --> 00:15:02,649
These are the most dangerous problems you
could face when trading, and it is important

188
00:15:02,649 --> 00:15:04,480
to seek professional help.

189
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:08,380
I had a friend that lost his house because
of this.

190
00:15:08,380 --> 00:15:15,060
It’s so easy to be caught up in this spiral,
and at the same time, it’s hard to get out,

191
00:15:15,060 --> 00:15:17,870
if things go out of control.

192
00:15:17,870 --> 00:15:23,970
Trading is demanding and it’s very important
to be aware and recognize the warning signs.

193
00:15:23,970 --> 00:15:31,740
These signs may include changes in mood, difficulty
sleeping, anxiety and difficulty concentrating.

194
00:15:31,740 --> 00:15:37,680
If you are experiencing any of these symptoms,
there’s no shame in seeking some professional

195
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:38,820
help.

196
00:15:38,820 --> 00:15:44,350
Trading should not take control over your
life and your mind.

197
00:15:44,350 --> 00:15:51,600
If you enjoyed learning about the role of
psychology in trading, be sure to check out

198
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:55,180
our next video on improving your trading psychology.

199
00:15:55,180 --> 00:16:00,339
And check out our academy program, if you
want to further level up your trading.

200
00:16:00,339 --> 00:16:01,500
Until next time!

